1
00:01:06,439 --> 00:01:07,000
Who's there?

2
00:01:12,799 --> 00:01:14,280
You're so noisy!

3
00:01:15,959 --> 00:01:16,359
Brother,

4
00:01:16,719 --> 00:01:18,480
why are there so many strange women around you?

5
00:01:20,319 --> 00:01:21,439
I'll leave this trouble to you.

6
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:23,599
Where's Jiang Yue?

7
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:24,959
You deal with it.

8
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:26,680
It's none of your business.

9
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:28,519
I knew it.

10
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:30,120
How could such an ordinary girl

11
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,599
be your girlfriend?

12
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:33,280
I'll tell my dad when I get back

13
00:01:33,439 --> 00:01:33,959
to send someone...

14
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:35,120
She is my girlfriend.

15
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,120
You're talking nonsense.

16
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:37,959
I'm telling you,

17
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,719
none of you can touch her.

18
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,480
Which lackey are you?

19
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,560
Your darts are so bad.

20
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,599
I'm his real brother.

21
00:01:56,799 --> 00:01:58,359
No wonder you look decent.

22
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:01,680
Tell your brother,

23
00:02:01,879 --> 00:02:02,959
I won't give up on him.

24
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:28,919
Hello,

25
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,319
I want to buy a phone.

26
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:31,400
Okay, sir.

27
00:02:31,759 --> 00:02:33,439
I heard this store is very famous.

28
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,400
The owner used to be the pastry chef at Hôtel Ritz Paris.

29
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,680
How about we go to France for our next trip?

30
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,120
Place Vendôme is very beautiful in autumn.

31
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:46,560
Moon?

32
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:52,120
What square?

33
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,120
Place Vendôme.

34
00:02:54,879 --> 00:02:56,000
There are Chanel

35
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,879
and Princess Diana's former residences.

36
00:03:01,439 --> 00:03:01,919
What's wrong?

37
00:03:04,759 --> 00:03:05,479
Nothing.

38
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:08,400
I just feel the air is too stuffy here.

39
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:09,520
I'm having a bit of trouble breathing.

40
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,479
Bro, I'm going out for some fresh air.

41
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,240
I'll be right back.

42
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:53,759
What flavor do you want?

43
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:55,759
A strawberry one, please.

44
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:56,279
Okay.

45
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:56,879
Thank you.

46
00:04:57,959 --> 00:04:58,959
Why do you want to move out?

47
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,399
Need some peace and quiet.

48
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:05,560
Right.

49
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,680
They are a bit noisy.

50
00:05:07,439 --> 00:05:08,360
No,

51
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,199
my brain needs to be quiet.

52
00:05:11,839 --> 00:05:13,439
There's been too much information these days.

53
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,120
I wish it was just a dream.

54
00:05:16,879 --> 00:05:17,639
You know,

55
00:05:17,759 --> 00:05:19,319
my brain feels like a carousel.

56
00:05:20,439 --> 00:05:22,600
My mind is full of Li Feiyuan.

57
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,120
Sorry

58
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,879
for involving you in the past.

59
00:05:29,959 --> 00:05:30,680
You know what?

60
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,839
When I met someone handing out samples,

61
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,319
My first reaction was to say thank you.

62
00:05:36,279 --> 00:05:38,120
Now I still want to drink tea when I'm thirsty.

63
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:41,079
I'm really split in personality.

64
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,199
Actually, Li Feiyuan now

65
00:05:43,199 --> 00:05:44,079
also has your shadow.

66
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:46,319
She uses your eyes to see the modern world,

67
00:05:46,399 --> 00:05:47,079
is not afraid of danger,

68
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,519
and is full of curiosity

69
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,439
about everything.

70
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:10,959
Hello,

71
00:06:11,759 --> 00:06:12,160
check out.

72
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,199
Okay, sir.

73
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:28,920
Let's

74
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,199
go home.

75
00:06:33,199 --> 00:06:35,079
[Are you sure you want to take Jiang Yue]

76
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:37,240
[or Li Feiyuan?]

77
00:06:40,199 --> 00:06:41,160
Stop messing around.

78
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:44,519
Actually, our consciousness

79
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:46,399
is like two ice creams.

80
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,839
It's hard to say if they'll melt together in the end.

81
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:53,120
Cang Feng and Li Feiyuan have very important memories.

82
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:57,040
This past is too heavy for me.

83
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,959
Even if I am her rebirth,

84
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:02,519
it doesn't mean I have to take on all this.

85
00:07:02,879 --> 00:07:04,160
[I won't hurt you anymore,]

86
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:07,600
[Lu Zhiyu.]

87
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,680
[I don't want to be]

88
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,079
[a shadow of someone else in front of you.]

89
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:17,560
[If your kindness towards me]

90
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,000
[is due to the Brand Bonding]

91
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,959
[rather than genuine,]

92
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,480
[that's not what I want either.]

93
00:07:30,879 --> 00:07:32,879
It seems the street vendor's ice cream is better.

94
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,360
I just had a chat with him.

95
00:07:37,759 --> 00:07:38,560
Now that we've finished talking,

96
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,639
let's go.

97
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:41,759
Wait.

98
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:48,759
Let's exchange WeChat.

99
00:07:49,279 --> 00:07:50,360
Didn't you finish talking?

100
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,480
Scan my code.

101
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,600
Looks like you're not very close.

102
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:07,800
Let's go.

103
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:19,199
It's true.

104
00:08:49,919 --> 00:08:50,759
We're home.

105
00:08:51,919 --> 00:08:53,320
Bro, why didn't you wake me up?

106
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:54,519
Let's go home.

107
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:55,600
I'll make you dinner.

108
00:09:12,399 --> 00:09:13,080
It's so good.

109
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:15,879
I thought

110
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,360
you were tired of my cooking.

111
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:18,679
How could that be?

112
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,559
Your fried eggs

113
00:09:20,639 --> 00:09:21,759
are the best.

114
00:09:23,639 --> 00:09:24,799
I remember when we were kids,

115
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,039
you liked doing homework in the kitchen.

116
00:09:29,039 --> 00:09:29,840
Because I think

117
00:09:29,919 --> 00:09:31,600
the kitchen is the warmest place.

118
00:09:32,519 --> 00:09:33,759
Our home was empty

119
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,159
and cold when we were kids.

120
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,919
But the noodles you made for me

121
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,279
It was delicious and warm.

122
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:44,679
By the way, Moon,

123
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:46,960
what do you want for your birthday this year?

124
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:49,840
I don't want anything.

125
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,639
I don't even know

126
00:09:54,759 --> 00:09:56,759
the exact date of my birth.

127
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,200
The date on my ID card

128
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,159
is just the date

129
00:09:59,279 --> 00:10:00,600
Uncle Xie adopted me.

130
00:10:00,759 --> 00:10:02,080
If you don't want to go home,

131
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,840
we can go somewhere further.

132
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,399
Go skiing

133
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,960
or see the aurora.

134
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,519
I'm almost done with my work anyway.

135
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,360
Brother,

136
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,519
how did you know Qin Yeren?

137
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,159
I don't know him well.

138
00:10:17,279 --> 00:10:18,159
Because you're here,

139
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:19,279
I made up an excuse

140
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,600
to tell Dad that I was on a business trip.

141
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,840
Since Qin Yeren is a local bully,

142
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,399
for the company's reputation,

143
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:26,159
I'll terminate the cooperation with him.

144
00:10:27,639 --> 00:10:28,679
Then I'm relieved.

145
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:29,279
Let's eat.

146
00:10:29,279 --> 00:10:29,919
I'm starving.

147
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:44,279
Lu Zhiyu,

148
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,240
if your kindness to me

149
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:47,720
is due to the Brand Bonding,

150
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,639
not from your heart,

151
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:53,080
that's not what I want.

152
00:10:55,039 --> 00:10:55,480
I...

153
00:10:57,399 --> 00:10:58,360
Is this a confession?

154
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,000
Don't think too much.

155
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,240
What if he just means it literally,

156
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,039
and claims to be honest and straightforward?

157
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:25,240
What do you mean?

158
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:35,000
The brand seems to be fading away.

159
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:52,039
This is a smartphone.

160
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,559
Human beings have no sense.

161
00:11:54,399 --> 00:11:55,759
We can make remote calls with this.

162
00:12:02,279 --> 00:12:02,840
This...

163
00:12:06,919 --> 00:12:08,000
Did you forget what I do?

164
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,720
I'm a bounty hunter.

165
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:13,120
I need to receive information anytime and anywhere.

166
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,039
It's so quiet tonight.

167
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,679
The noisy Zhang San is not here.

168
00:12:22,759 --> 00:12:24,440
They went to stand guard near Jiang Yue's house.

169
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,080
We take turns on watch.

170
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,639
No killer can get close.

171
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,879
That's what I'm telling you.

172
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:34,559
Don't have any bad thoughts.

173
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:38,039
I really don't understand your thought process.

174
00:12:38,679 --> 00:12:39,919
You let that Li Feiyuan...

175
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,039
All right, Jiang Yue.

176
00:12:42,919 --> 00:12:44,039
Let her run away.

177
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:45,559
And watch her like a guard.

178
00:12:46,159 --> 00:12:46,679
And

179
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:48,919
investigate Qin Yeren's business network.

180
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,919
His daughter came to you for help.

181
00:12:51,399 --> 00:12:53,080
and you just let her go.

182
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,200
You mean

183
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,879
I should have arrested Qin Yaxin

184
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,120
as a hostage.

185
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,080
She has such a bad temper.

186
00:13:01,759 --> 00:13:02,960
Isn't it reasonable for her to suffer a bit?

187
00:13:03,519 --> 00:13:04,360
From what she said,

188
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:06,159
she doesn't know what her father is doing.

189
00:13:06,639 --> 00:13:07,720
What her father did

190
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:08,720
has nothing to do with her.

191
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,080
Frankly,

192
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,519
you just want to persuade me not to take revenge.

193
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:29,600
Silly dog.

194
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,639
What are you doing?

195
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,000
See?

196
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,559
Smartphones are addictive.

197
00:13:44,279 --> 00:13:45,120
Why is it suddenly dark?

198
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,799
You played the phone until it ran out of battery, right?

199
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:48,399
I just don't use the phone,

200
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:49,720
not an idiot about electronics.

201
00:13:50,519 --> 00:13:52,240
Why did you buy such an old model?

202
00:13:54,279 --> 00:13:55,399
This is the same model as Jiang Yue's.

203
00:13:56,559 --> 00:13:57,840
The signal should be better.

204
00:14:05,519 --> 00:14:06,840
Do you even know how to use a phone?

205
00:15:01,879 --> 00:15:02,320
Bro,

206
00:15:02,799 --> 00:15:04,159
I've got the invitation cards.

207
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:05,759
But they require

208
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,080
the guests to dress up.

209
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,120
It doesn't matter.

210
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:10,960
I heard

211
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,320
Miss Jiang would also go there.

212
00:15:23,559 --> 00:15:24,039
Is it okay?

213
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:42,039
This is what I wore at my friend's wedding.

214
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:58,840
I killed a tiger

215
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,120
in this suit.

216
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:04,519
This is good.

217
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:05,799
Are you sure?

218
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:09,080
The formal dress of the Wolf Clan is also a formal dress.

219
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:10,799
Okay.
